Looking at this proof goal, I need to prove that `spine (foldl node (node (leaf x) t) ts) = leaf x :: t :: ts` given the induction hypothesis `spine (foldl node (leaf x) ts) = leaf x :: ts`.

The key insight is that I need a more general lemma about how `spine` interacts with `foldl node`. Let me work through this:

```lean
example [Inhabited a] (ts : List (Tree a)) :
 spine (rollup ([Tree.leaf x] ++ ts)) = [Tree.leaf x] ++ ts := by
  induction ts with
  | nil =>
    simp [rollup, foldl1, spine]
  | cons t ts ih =>
    simp [rollup, foldl1, List.foldl]
    simp [rollup, foldl1] at ih
    have gen : ∀ (u : Tree a) (vs : List (Tree a)), 
      spine (List.foldl Tree.node u vs) = spine u ++ vs := by
      intro u vs
      induction vs generalizing u with
      | nil => simp
      | cons v vs ihv => 
        simp [List.foldl]
        rw [ihv]
        simp [spine]
    rw [gen]
    simp [spine]
```
